Tenth Avenue, west side, north from W. 35th Street, showing the Bethany Congregationalist Church at No. 455-9. In 1938 this structure is being used by the W.P.A. as a Theatre work shop. The 13 story building shown at the N.W. corner of 36th Street is occupied by the McGraw Hill Publishing Co. and is No. 459-75 Tenth
Avenue.
Views 2 and 3 show the Church building solely.
October 31, 1931
View 2:May 27, 1930
View 3:May 24, 1929.
P.L. Sperr

Tenth Avenue, west side, south from W. 36th to 35th Streets, showing the former Bethany Congregationalist Church in the middle of this block. It is now being used by the W..A. as a theatre work shop aft-r recent abandonment. This structure bears No. 455-9 Tenth Avenue and the tenements at the corner (N.W. of 35th Street)
No's. 451 and 453.
